1
00:00:11,417 --> 00:00:14,083
- [EMT] Make way! Clear a path!
- [nurse] Coming through! Excuse me.

2
00:00:14,167 --> 00:00:17,083
- [EMT] Coming through!
- [nurse] Make way! Excuse me.

3
00:00:17,167 --> 00:00:19,042
[muffled] Make way! Move aside!

4
00:00:19,125 --> 00:00:21,042
Clear a path! Please make way!

5
00:00:21,125 --> 00:00:22,583
[nurse] We have an emergency!

6
00:00:22,667 --> 00:00:24,875
She's heavily pregnant!
She was in an accident.

7
00:00:24,958 --> 00:00:26,458
[tense music playing]

8
00:00:28,625 --> 00:00:31,500
- [nurse 1] BP 80/50. Pulse 130.
- [nurse 2] Have you drawn the labs?

9
00:00:31,583 --> 00:00:32,708
[nurse 1] They've been sent.

10
00:00:32,792 --> 00:00:34,542
[nurse 2] IV is running.
Sat's dropping to 88.

11
00:00:34,625 --> 00:00:35,708
The doctor is here.

12
00:00:35,792 --> 00:00:37,417
[doctor] How does the fetal heart sound?

13
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:38,750
[nurse 2] It sounds faint.

14
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:40,333
[nurse 3] Sat's down to 75.

15
00:00:40,417 --> 00:00:41,625
[doctor] Get the FAST.

16
00:00:41,708 --> 00:00:43,167
[nurse 2] Go get the FAST!

17
00:00:43,875 --> 00:00:45,833
[weakly] Please, save my baby.

18
00:00:48,625 --> 00:00:50,417
[nurse 3] Her consciousness is dropping.

19
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:52,333
[doctor] FAST is positive.

20
00:00:52,417 --> 00:00:54,083
Notify the OR. Don't wait.

21
00:00:56,625 --> 00:00:59,583
[music concludes]

22
00:00:59,667 --> 00:01:02,208
[Yupin speaking indistinctly]

23
00:01:03,625 --> 00:01:05,750
The other car was going very fast.

24
00:01:05,833 --> 00:01:06,750
[sniffles]

25
00:01:07,250 --> 00:01:10,292
The police said the driver was drunk.

26
00:01:10,917 --> 00:01:13,167
When I got to the hospital… [sniffles]

27
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:16,792
…I was rushed in
for an emergency C-section.

28
00:01:19,375 --> 00:01:20,708
[sobs softly]

29
00:01:22,042 --> 00:01:25,042
I didn't even get to see my baby's face.

30
00:01:26,458 --> 00:01:27,333
[whimpers]

31
00:01:27,875 --> 00:01:29,500
And my baby…

32
00:01:30,208 --> 00:01:33,375
Witness, when did you find out

33
00:01:33,458 --> 00:01:35,375
that your baby's body was missing?

34
00:01:36,083 --> 00:01:37,500
[sniffles]

35
00:01:38,125 --> 00:01:39,042
[exhales]

36
00:01:40,375 --> 00:01:43,500
On the day of the cremation,
I asked to have the coffin opened.

37
00:01:44,708 --> 00:01:45,708
But…

38
00:01:46,625 --> 00:01:48,958
the undertaker wouldn't let me see.

39
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:53,208
So I had to threaten to call the police.

40
00:01:53,292 --> 00:01:55,458
That's when he finally admitted to me…

41
00:01:56,917 --> 00:01:57,917
[sniffles]

42
00:01:58,500 --> 00:02:00,500
…that he took my baby's body

43
00:02:00,583 --> 00:02:02,625
and sold it to that man, Boonlue.

44
00:02:02,708 --> 00:02:04,542
[sinister music playing]

45
00:02:10,792 --> 00:02:12,667
This image is from Exhibit VJ-7.

46
00:02:13,417 --> 00:02:16,375
It shows the defendant's monastery
during the police raid.

47
00:02:17,250 --> 00:02:19,167
Witness, have you ever been there?

48
00:02:19,792 --> 00:02:21,167
Please tell the court about it.

49
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:22,208
[Yupin] Yes.

50
00:02:22,292 --> 00:02:24,625
I went there looking for my baby.

51
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:26,958
With the police.

52
00:02:28,208 --> 00:02:32,000
[lawyer] From Exhibits VJ-8
through VJ-12…

53
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:36,708
Witness, do you know
what is in these photos?

54
00:02:36,792 --> 00:02:37,750
[sniffles]

55
00:02:40,208 --> 00:02:41,708
[breathes shakily]

56
00:02:41,792 --> 00:02:43,542
That's my baby.

57
00:02:43,625 --> 00:02:46,583
- [music intensifies]
- [Yupin] He turned him into a <i>luk krok</i>.

58
00:02:48,583 --> 00:02:50,125
My baby…

59
00:02:51,958 --> 00:02:54,625
He was inside me for nine months.

60
00:02:55,708 --> 00:02:56,583
[sobs]

61
00:02:56,667 --> 00:02:58,167
But in the end…

62
00:03:01,875 --> 00:03:03,167
You!

63
00:03:03,250 --> 00:03:05,500
You turned my son into a talisman
and sold him!

64
00:03:05,583 --> 00:03:07,125
How could you do that, you bastard?!

65
00:03:07,208 --> 00:03:08,750
Witness, compose yourself.

66
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:11,500
[Yupin] That was my son!
I lost both my son and my husband!

67
00:03:11,583 --> 00:03:14,250
Are you even human, you animal?!

68
00:03:14,917 --> 00:03:16,292
Damn you to hell!

69
00:03:17,250 --> 00:03:18,250
Yupin.

70
00:03:18,958 --> 00:03:20,292
Yupin.

71
00:03:20,375 --> 00:03:22,083
Calm down. Calm down, Yupin.

72
00:03:22,167 --> 00:03:23,375
Calm down.

73
00:03:23,458 --> 00:03:26,292
- [music fades]
- [breathes shakily]

74
00:03:30,667 --> 00:03:31,542
[sniffles]

75
00:03:31,625 --> 00:03:33,000
No further questions.

76
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:35,875
The defense may cross-examine.

77
00:03:40,875 --> 00:03:43,000
Does the defense have no questions?

78
00:03:50,458 --> 00:03:51,625
No questions, Your Honor.

79
00:03:51,708 --> 00:03:54,500
- [judge] Are you sure?
- [Jittri] Yes, Your Honor.

80
00:03:54,583 --> 00:03:56,917
[unsettling music playing]

81
00:04:00,042 --> 00:04:02,125
[judge] Call the next witness.

82
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:08,167
Witness, what is your connection
to this case?

83
00:04:08,250 --> 00:04:11,458
I'm the doctor who delivered the baby
by C-section after the accident.

84
00:04:11,542 --> 00:04:14,167
[lawyer] And what was
the fetus's condition at that time?

85
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:16,958
Critical. The mother's uterus
had ruptured.

86
00:04:17,042 --> 00:04:20,375
The mother was losing a lot of blood.
If we didn't operate immediately,

87
00:04:20,458 --> 00:04:23,333
there was a high probability
that we would lose them both.

88
00:04:25,250 --> 00:04:26,708
But as we all know,

89
00:04:27,958 --> 00:04:30,917
in the end, we were only able
to save the mother.

90
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,125
And what happened to the baby after that?

91
00:04:33,208 --> 00:04:34,792
[doctor] We informed the mother

92
00:04:34,875 --> 00:04:36,625
that the body was still at the hospital

93
00:04:36,708 --> 00:04:38,625
before it was sent

94
00:04:38,708 --> 00:04:41,375
to the temple where the incident occurred.

95
00:04:42,083 --> 00:04:43,583
[lawyer] No further questions.

96
00:04:44,458 --> 00:04:45,417
[music fades]

97
00:04:45,500 --> 00:04:47,833
[judge] Will the defense
be questioning this witness?

98
00:04:47,917 --> 00:04:50,625
I will be questioning this witness myself,
Your Honor.

99
00:04:51,625 --> 00:04:52,958
[high heels clacking]

100
00:04:53,042 --> 00:04:55,708
[tense music playing]

101
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:01,292
After you delivered the baby,
did it make a sound?

102
00:05:04,667 --> 00:05:05,833
No.

103
00:05:06,625 --> 00:05:08,833
And the baby's body,
when you delivered it,

104
00:05:08,917 --> 00:05:11,000
do you recall what color it was?

105
00:05:11,583 --> 00:05:13,750
[high-pitched ringing]

106
00:05:13,833 --> 00:05:15,708
- [footsteps approaching]
- [EKG monitor beeping]

107
00:05:15,792 --> 00:05:17,500
[lights slam off]

108
00:05:23,750 --> 00:05:25,125
What color was it?

109
00:05:25,208 --> 00:05:27,667
Green or purple?

110
00:05:32,083 --> 00:05:33,458
[doctor] It was discolored.

111
00:05:37,417 --> 00:05:41,083
[Jittri] After you delivered the baby,
did it move at all?

112
00:05:41,167 --> 00:05:43,417
[pediatrician] No heart rate.
Prepare for PPV.

113
00:05:47,542 --> 00:05:49,083
I don't know the specifics.

114
00:05:49,167 --> 00:05:50,417
I'm an obstetrician.

115
00:05:51,125 --> 00:05:52,375
Once the delivery was complete,

116
00:05:52,458 --> 00:05:54,375
it became
the pediatrician's responsibility.

117
00:05:54,458 --> 00:05:57,458
[pediatrician] No improvement.
Prep 0.01 milligrams of adrenaline.

118
00:05:57,542 --> 00:06:00,083
[Jittri] After the baby was delivered,

119
00:06:00,167 --> 00:06:02,542
no matter what life-saving measures
were attempted,

120
00:06:02,625 --> 00:06:05,292
a pulse was never detected.
Is that correct?

121
00:06:07,292 --> 00:06:09,708
[machine beeping]

122
00:06:09,792 --> 00:06:12,500
[pediatrician] Still no heart rate.
Stop resuscitation.

123
00:06:13,875 --> 00:06:15,458
Please answer yes or no.

124
00:06:18,042 --> 00:06:19,417
Yes.

125
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:23,542
[Jittri] Medically speaking,

126
00:06:24,375 --> 00:06:26,250
an infant in this condition

127
00:06:27,958 --> 00:06:30,250
is considered a stillbirth.

128
00:06:30,958 --> 00:06:32,333
Yes or no?

129
00:06:32,417 --> 00:06:34,083
[music rises]

130
00:06:34,167 --> 00:06:35,500
[lawyer] Objection.

131
00:06:35,583 --> 00:06:37,417
Counsel's question is irrelevant.

132
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:38,917
It has no bearing on the case.

133
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:42,083
The charges filed are not related
to the time of the infant's death.

134
00:06:42,167 --> 00:06:44,375
I assure you,
my question is not irrelevant.

135
00:06:44,458 --> 00:06:46,083
Because my point is…

136
00:06:46,167 --> 00:06:48,458
How can you say the child died,

137
00:06:48,542 --> 00:06:50,417
when the child was never alive?

138
00:06:51,708 --> 00:06:55,625
[crowd murmuring]

139
00:06:56,417 --> 00:06:58,125
[judge] Order, please.

140
00:06:59,333 --> 00:07:01,042
Counselor.

141
00:07:01,125 --> 00:07:03,958
Please adhere to the relevant issues.

142
00:07:04,042 --> 00:07:05,333
Yes, Your Honor.

143
00:07:07,208 --> 00:07:09,417
This is Ms. Yupin's medical record.

144
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:12,458
It states here that the infant
had no vital signs after birth.

145
00:07:12,542 --> 00:07:14,000
So from the moment of birth,

146
00:07:14,083 --> 00:07:16,500
the infant was already deceased.
Is that correct?

147
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:22,875
[judge] Witness.
Don't look at anyone else.

148
00:07:22,958 --> 00:07:24,875
Just answer the question truthfully.

149
00:07:28,542 --> 00:07:29,917
That's correct.

150
00:07:31,417 --> 00:07:33,417
[Jittri] Please record that, Your Honor.

151
00:07:34,833 --> 00:07:36,958
[judge] Infant had
no vital signs after birth,

152
00:07:37,042 --> 00:07:38,667
meaning the infant was deceased.

153
00:07:40,792 --> 00:07:42,667
[Jittri] These are images
of a stillborn infant

154
00:07:42,750 --> 00:07:45,000
who died before attaining
legal personhood.

155
00:07:45,083 --> 00:07:48,708
Legal personhood begins when a child
is born and survives delivery.

156
00:07:48,792 --> 00:07:51,125
In Ms. Yupin's case, after the delivery,

157
00:07:51,208 --> 00:07:53,250
the doctor detected no pulse.

158
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:56,292
There were no signs of life
while it was still in the womb.

159
00:07:56,375 --> 00:07:59,042
That means the infant that was delivered

160
00:07:59,125 --> 00:08:00,625
cannot be legally defined as a corpse,

161
00:08:00,708 --> 00:08:02,583
but rather, as remains,

162
00:08:02,667 --> 00:08:04,542
which is no different from
a scrap of flesh.

163
00:08:04,625 --> 00:08:06,500
- [music darkens]
- [crowd gasping]

164
00:08:06,583 --> 00:08:08,625
[crowd murmuring]

165
00:08:09,958 --> 00:08:12,708
[lawyer] Are you calling a child
who was weeks away from being born

166
00:08:12,792 --> 00:08:14,125
a scrap of flesh?

167
00:08:14,208 --> 00:08:15,875
We're talking about a human being.

168
00:08:15,958 --> 00:08:17,125
Any birth certificate?

169
00:08:17,875 --> 00:08:19,875
If you claim these remains are a person.

170
00:08:21,375 --> 00:08:24,583
- [music falls]
- I'm aware my words may sound harsh.

171
00:08:24,667 --> 00:08:27,208
But believe me when I say I do sympathize.

172
00:08:27,292 --> 00:08:28,792
I see my own assistant,

173
00:08:28,875 --> 00:08:31,250
cherishing the child in her womb
every day.

174
00:08:31,833 --> 00:08:33,792
Do you really think I don't understand

175
00:08:33,875 --> 00:08:35,792
what it feels like to become a mother?

176
00:08:35,875 --> 00:08:37,458
How profound that feeling is?

177
00:08:37,542 --> 00:08:40,917
Objection. The defense is twisting
the law to suit her.

178
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,875
Her interpretation is inadmissible.

179
00:08:43,542 --> 00:08:45,417
Whether this is a matter of legal debate

180
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:47,333
is for the court to decide.

181
00:08:47,417 --> 00:08:49,167
Counselor, you may proceed.

182
00:08:49,250 --> 00:08:51,417
Then I have one final question.

183
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:55,167
The prosecution has filed charges
under Section 199

184
00:08:55,250 --> 00:08:58,375
and Section 366, subsection 3,
for desecration of a corpse.

185
00:08:58,458 --> 00:09:00,833
If it's proven these are merely remains,

186
00:09:00,917 --> 00:09:03,208
would that constitute a false indictment

187
00:09:03,292 --> 00:09:05,083
and require this case to be dismissed?

188
00:09:05,167 --> 00:09:06,833
[music rises]

189
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,917
[music crescendoes]

190
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,500
[music fades]

191
00:09:23,250 --> 00:09:24,208
[Boonlue] Impressive.

192
00:09:24,292 --> 00:09:25,542
Excellent work.

193
00:09:27,708 --> 00:09:29,042
Okay, that's all for now.

194
00:09:31,458 --> 00:09:33,208
Mr. Suwat sends his thanks.

195
00:09:33,708 --> 00:09:36,625
He'd like you to join him for wine
at his home in Prachinburi.

196
00:09:36,708 --> 00:09:39,542
There are plenty of other cases
he'd like your help with.

197
00:09:40,208 --> 00:09:41,417
Of course.

198
00:09:43,542 --> 00:09:45,042
So, when are you due?

199
00:09:46,667 --> 00:09:48,250
Please let him know

200
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:50,417
that I will contact his secretary myself.

201
00:09:52,750 --> 00:09:54,708
Alright. Be sure to get in touch.

202
00:09:54,792 --> 00:09:56,000
I will.

203
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,042
I quit.

204
00:10:12,542 --> 00:10:15,292
I thought working for you
would make me a better person.

205
00:10:16,125 --> 00:10:18,542
But the longer I'm here,
the more I hate myself.

206
00:10:19,458 --> 00:10:21,750
You're disgusting. Don't you see that?

207
00:10:22,833 --> 00:10:25,125
I'm simply doing what the law allows.

208
00:10:26,042 --> 00:10:29,792
If what I do is evil, then everyone
in this building is evil too. Right?

209
00:10:31,042 --> 00:10:32,000
[scoffs]

210
00:10:32,875 --> 00:10:34,125
[Jittri] You want to argue?

211
00:10:34,208 --> 00:10:35,583
[tense music playing]

212
00:10:35,667 --> 00:10:38,458
Society is screwed up
because of people like you.

213
00:10:38,542 --> 00:10:40,708
Getting pregnant has made you
so sensitive.

214
00:10:41,667 --> 00:10:42,833
Whatever.

215
00:10:43,417 --> 00:10:46,875
But next time I have a case
involving a mother and child, I'll call.

216
00:10:47,542 --> 00:10:49,917
Maybe if you're pregnant again,
we can work together.

217
00:10:57,083 --> 00:10:58,542
[Jittri] Pick it up yourself.

218
00:11:03,042 --> 00:11:05,625
- [music darkens]
- [detector beeping]

219
00:11:06,917 --> 00:11:09,250
[reporter 1] She's here!
Ms. Jittri, a quick comment?

220
00:11:09,333 --> 00:11:11,250
[reporter 2] Is it true
a politician is involved

221
00:11:11,333 --> 00:11:12,833
in this infant corpse trafficking ring?

222
00:11:12,917 --> 00:11:15,792
[reporter 3] There's talk on social media
about putting a bounty on you.

223
00:11:15,875 --> 00:11:17,042
Does that concern you?

224
00:11:17,125 --> 00:11:19,167
[reporter 4]
All these questions and no comments?

225
00:11:19,250 --> 00:11:21,417
Is someone powerful
pulling the strings on this case?

226
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:24,375
Jittri! You said my baby
was just remains, not a person?

227
00:11:24,458 --> 00:11:26,042
- You bitch!
- [bystander screams]

228
00:11:28,708 --> 00:11:30,083
[Yupin] How could you do that?

229
00:11:30,167 --> 00:11:32,000
Huh?! How could you?

230
00:11:32,083 --> 00:11:35,792
- You animal! Are you happy now?
- [reporters clamoring]

231
00:11:35,875 --> 00:11:37,667
[Yupin] Did you buy your law degree?

232
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:39,208
Do you have any humanity in you?

233
00:11:39,292 --> 00:11:42,417
Huh? That was my child, you animal!

234
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:44,625
Are you even human?

235
00:11:44,708 --> 00:11:46,500
I carried my baby for nine months!

236
00:11:46,583 --> 00:11:48,500
I was about to give birth!

237
00:11:48,583 --> 00:11:50,292
What is your heart made of?

238
00:11:51,083 --> 00:11:53,667
My baby was right here in my womb!

239
00:11:53,750 --> 00:11:55,958
Get all of this! Keep rolling!

240
00:11:57,083 --> 00:11:58,333
What the hell?

241
00:11:58,417 --> 00:12:01,333
- [Yupin sobbing]
- [dark intriguing music playing]

242
00:12:03,792 --> 00:12:05,833
[dark intriguing music continues]

243
00:12:08,750 --> 00:12:14,667
THE EVIL LAWYER

244
00:12:14,750 --> 00:12:16,667
[music fades]

245
00:12:19,583 --> 00:12:22,458
[brooding music playing]

246
00:12:24,333 --> 00:12:25,417
[detector beeps]

247
00:12:34,833 --> 00:12:37,542
[indistinct chatter]

248
00:12:37,625 --> 00:12:39,542
[clerk 1] She got it all over herself.

249
00:12:39,625 --> 00:12:41,833
[clerk 2] That woman
looked so angry, though.

250
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:45,958
[phone ringing]

251
00:12:46,042 --> 00:12:47,542
[clerk 1] Oh my god.

252
00:12:48,917 --> 00:12:51,125
- How could she not be?
- [clerk 2] Will it come off?

253
00:12:51,208 --> 00:12:53,333
[clerk 1] Well, look who it is.
The celebrity.

254
00:12:53,417 --> 00:12:54,875
[Mek] What are you talking about?

255
00:12:54,958 --> 00:12:56,000
[clerk 1 chuckles]

256
00:12:56,083 --> 00:12:58,333
- [music fades]
- This is why you're famous. Look.

257
00:12:58,958 --> 00:13:01,625
You really shone on the live stream.

258
00:13:03,042 --> 00:13:05,083
Can I have your autograph? [chuckles]

259
00:13:06,083 --> 00:13:08,292
Man, I feel bad for her.

260
00:13:08,375 --> 00:13:10,792
[clerk 2] If it were me,
she'd get more than just pig's blood.

261
00:13:10,875 --> 00:13:13,417
I would've thrown in some guts too.

262
00:13:14,542 --> 00:13:17,375
I don't know
how she can even sleep at night.

263
00:13:17,458 --> 00:13:19,208
[Tong] Don't joke about that.

264
00:13:19,292 --> 00:13:22,750
She's got a heavy caseload,
and they're all major cases.

265
00:13:23,417 --> 00:13:25,125
[clerk 1] You want to be like her, huh?

266
00:13:25,208 --> 00:13:27,792
Tong, look at the cases she takes on.

267
00:13:27,875 --> 00:13:30,292
This time it's a shaman.
What was it last time?

268
00:13:30,375 --> 00:13:33,083
[Tong] Last time was the colonel
who opened a pub for money laundering.

269
00:13:33,167 --> 00:13:34,583
[clerk 2] No, you're wrong.

270
00:13:34,667 --> 00:13:37,292
Before that was the tycoon who shot
his son-in-law at the wedding.

271
00:13:37,375 --> 00:13:40,250
And it was that lawyer, Jittri,
who got the tycoon acquitted.

272
00:13:40,333 --> 00:13:43,583
The evidence was airtight,
but she still got the defendant acquitted.

273
00:13:43,667 --> 00:13:45,542
She didn't do it by the book.

274
00:13:45,625 --> 00:13:47,833
True. People like that are scary.

275
00:13:48,333 --> 00:13:50,500
And look, you just walked past her.

276
00:13:53,042 --> 00:13:55,000
I can just wash it when I get home.

277
00:13:55,083 --> 00:13:58,458
Oh, Mek, I forgot to tell you.
You only have one case left today.

278
00:13:59,333 --> 00:14:01,958
The recycling plant fire case.

279
00:14:02,042 --> 00:14:03,625
The plant owner is the defendant.

280
00:14:03,708 --> 00:14:06,250
He's already confessed
during the investigation.

281
00:14:06,833 --> 00:14:09,958
So I just have to stand there
while the defendant confesses?

282
00:14:10,042 --> 00:14:13,000
Whoa, don't work yourself too hard.

283
00:14:13,083 --> 00:14:15,042
The arraignment is this afternoon.

284
00:14:16,167 --> 00:14:19,583
Have some water. Your mouth must be dry.

285
00:14:19,667 --> 00:14:21,042
[Mek] What's this about?

286
00:14:21,667 --> 00:14:24,875
How long are you going to be stuck
doing these public cases, Mek?

287
00:14:25,375 --> 00:14:27,250
Anyway, what about
the Lawyers' Rights Center?

288
00:14:27,333 --> 00:14:30,458
Haven't they asked you to come back?
I heard they're short-staffed.

289
00:14:30,542 --> 00:14:33,333
I'm staying here.
We're short-staffed here too.

290
00:14:33,417 --> 00:14:34,917
Oh, wow.

291
00:14:35,458 --> 00:14:38,458
If you're heartbroken,
you can always stay here with us, son.

292
00:14:39,375 --> 00:14:40,417
I'm getting back to work.

293
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:43,083
If you're looking for…
like, a girlfriend, right?

294
00:14:43,167 --> 00:14:46,083
Like a new girlfriend or something.
You can ask me for help with that.

295
00:14:46,167 --> 00:14:47,792
- I can find you one.
- What?

296
00:14:49,875 --> 00:14:51,458
Another failed sales pitch.

297
00:14:52,125 --> 00:14:54,083
- You were selling something?
- [clerk 2] Yep.

298
00:14:54,167 --> 00:14:56,833
- Here, take this back.
- I can give you a discount. Mine is a…

299
00:14:56,917 --> 00:14:58,333
It's a pre-order for now.

300
00:14:58,833 --> 00:14:59,750
[clerk 1 mutters]

301
00:15:01,792 --> 00:15:03,250
[Mek] Excuse me, are you Aon?

302
00:15:07,500 --> 00:15:09,000
My name is Mek.

303
00:15:09,083 --> 00:15:11,250
I'm your father's lawyer.

304
00:15:11,333 --> 00:15:13,125
I've read the preliminary file, but…

305
00:15:13,208 --> 00:15:14,750
Just like my dad told the police.

306
00:15:14,833 --> 00:15:16,667
Whatever he said, that's what it is.

307
00:15:18,458 --> 00:15:21,333
About your father's confession,
there's a part at the end that I found…

308
00:15:21,417 --> 00:15:23,042
That's right. Just go with that.

309
00:15:25,125 --> 00:15:28,250
Sir, I compared your father's case
to others with similar circumstances.

310
00:15:28,333 --> 00:15:30,000
My dad is ready to take responsibility.

311
00:15:30,083 --> 00:15:31,917
He's willing to go to prison.

312
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:34,000
So can we just get this over with?

313
00:15:36,458 --> 00:15:39,542
What I'm trying to say is,
the maximum sentence is seven years.

314
00:15:39,625 --> 00:15:41,542
And the file says, at your father's age

315
00:15:41,625 --> 00:15:43,958
and his current health,
prison will be hard on him.

316
00:15:44,042 --> 00:15:45,083
Listen, kid.

317
00:15:45,167 --> 00:15:47,792
I have a job to get to too.

318
00:15:47,875 --> 00:15:50,333
I don't have to be in court
every day like you.

319
00:15:50,417 --> 00:15:53,208
What's your problem?
Don't you want this to end quickly, huh?

320
00:15:53,292 --> 00:15:55,125
Trying to get more court fees?

321
00:15:55,958 --> 00:15:57,917
My dad already confessed.

322
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:00,750
Just go in there and look the part.
So we can get it done.

323
00:16:00,833 --> 00:16:02,875
[intriguing music playing]

324
00:16:04,625 --> 00:16:05,792
[Aon] Did you transfer it yet?

325
00:16:07,625 --> 00:16:10,292
Case number O.12/2568.

326
00:16:10,375 --> 00:16:11,917
Mr. Panitarn Boonprayook,

327
00:16:12,500 --> 00:16:15,917
the Managing Director
of Rungruang E-waste Recycling Factory.

328
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:19,792
The prosecutor has filed charges
of criminal negligence causing a fire.

329
00:16:19,875 --> 00:16:21,875
Resulting in the death of another person.

330
00:16:21,958 --> 00:16:23,375
And loss of property.

331
00:16:23,458 --> 00:16:25,292
The penalty is up to seven years in prison

332
00:16:25,375 --> 00:16:27,667
and a fine of up to 140,000 baht.

333
00:16:27,750 --> 00:16:30,875
In addition, the victims have gathered
to file for damages

334
00:16:30,958 --> 00:16:33,292
for an additional ten million baht.

335
00:16:33,375 --> 00:16:35,542
The plaintiff's attorney
is present for the civil case,

336
00:16:35,625 --> 00:16:37,167
which is related to the criminal case.

337
00:16:37,250 --> 00:16:38,792
- [music fades]
- Yes, Your Honor.

338
00:16:38,875 --> 00:16:41,208
This case involves
a large number of victims.

339
00:16:41,292 --> 00:16:44,375
And I have been appointed
to represent them in this lawsuit.

340
00:16:44,458 --> 00:16:47,167
Does the defendant plead guilty
or not guilty?

341
00:16:56,208 --> 00:16:57,417
Guilty.

342
00:16:57,500 --> 00:16:58,708
If I may, Your Honor.

343
00:16:59,625 --> 00:17:02,375
Uh, may I have a moment
to speak with my client?

344
00:17:02,458 --> 00:17:03,917
You may.

345
00:17:05,750 --> 00:17:08,625
Sir, did the other lawyer say
anything to you?

346
00:17:09,250 --> 00:17:11,750
If you didn't do it, you have to say so.

347
00:17:11,833 --> 00:17:13,083
I can help you.

348
00:17:14,375 --> 00:17:16,875
[Techin] The defendant confessed
during the initial investigation.

349
00:17:16,958 --> 00:17:18,708
That shows he feels remorse.

350
00:17:18,792 --> 00:17:20,958
And he truly wants to take responsibility.

351
00:17:22,167 --> 00:17:24,833
I don't know what tricks
you're trying, counselor.

352
00:17:24,917 --> 00:17:26,375
But even if you get him off,

353
00:17:26,458 --> 00:17:27,917
he'll live with the guilt for life,

354
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:30,500
which might be even worse than prison.

355
00:17:34,625 --> 00:17:37,292
[judge] So, does the defendant
stand by his statement?

356
00:17:39,167 --> 00:17:40,167
Sir…

357
00:17:41,542 --> 00:17:42,542
Yes, Your Honor.

358
00:17:43,750 --> 00:17:45,583
I plead guilty to all charges.

359
00:17:50,250 --> 00:17:52,417
Why the hell are you so invested in this?

360
00:17:52,958 --> 00:17:55,417
It's a public defender case.
Just get it over with.

361
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:57,750
So you can move on to other cases.

362
00:17:58,500 --> 00:18:00,458
And you? Don't you feel a damn thing?

363
00:18:00,542 --> 00:18:02,000
You just sent that man to prison.

364
00:18:02,792 --> 00:18:06,042
Whoa, hold on. You've got it all wrong.

365
00:18:06,125 --> 00:18:07,500
What am I supposed to feel?

366
00:18:07,583 --> 00:18:09,917
The man confessed. You also heard him.

367
00:18:10,875 --> 00:18:13,625
Look at him. Does he look like
a factory owner to you?

368
00:18:13,708 --> 00:18:17,250
Wow, Mek. You've really changed.

369
00:18:17,333 --> 00:18:19,792
Judging people
by their appearance now? [chuckles]

370
00:18:20,375 --> 00:18:22,875
Shouldn't a human rights lawyer
be more PC?

371
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:26,000
Ever heard of "Gold wrapped in rags"?

372
00:18:27,792 --> 00:18:31,125
Come on, man. What are you so mad about?

373
00:18:31,708 --> 00:18:34,792
The villagers got their compensation,
and you get paid.

374
00:18:35,375 --> 00:18:38,167
Isn't that a good thing?
Look at you, you're wasting away.

375
00:18:38,250 --> 00:18:40,625
Oh, you poor thing.

376
00:18:40,708 --> 00:18:42,833
You really think this is over?

377
00:18:42,917 --> 00:18:44,208
You just wait.

378
00:18:44,292 --> 00:18:46,458
[foreboding music playing]

379
00:18:47,125 --> 00:18:48,875
Where should I wait for you, Mek?

380
00:18:48,958 --> 00:18:52,167
Right here? Or inside the courtroom?
It's hot out here.

381
00:18:52,250 --> 00:18:53,583
<i>For an update on the story,</i>

382
00:18:53,667 --> 00:18:56,667
<i>regarding the fire</i>
<i>at the e-waste recycling plant,</i>

383
00:18:56,750 --> 00:18:58,917
<i>- Rungruang E-Waste Recycling.</i>
- [intriguing music playing]

384
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:01,500
[reporter]<i> The incident caused</i>
<i>extensive damage to the residents</i>

385
00:19:01,583 --> 00:19:03,167
<i>of the Lat Krabang community.</i>

386
00:19:03,250 --> 00:19:06,958
<i>Legal proceedings are now underway</i>
<i>against the factory's owner</i>

387
00:19:07,042 --> 00:19:09,833
<i>on charges of arson.</i>

388
00:19:09,917 --> 00:19:12,125
- [music fades]
- [metal clanging]

389
00:19:12,208 --> 00:19:14,625
[overlapping chatter]

390
00:19:14,708 --> 00:19:16,458
[man] Please form a line. Right this way.

391
00:19:16,542 --> 00:19:18,542
[overlapping chatter]

392
00:19:18,625 --> 00:19:20,417
- [reporter] One more photo, please.
- Of course.

393
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:22,917
- [camera shutters clicking]
- [soft tense music playing]

394
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:26,125
RUAM THAI PARTY
DONATES 1,000,000 BAHT

395
00:19:26,208 --> 00:19:27,417
[reporter] Okay, we're all set.

396
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:29,542
Thank you so much. Thank you.

397
00:19:29,625 --> 00:19:32,208
Don't go yet, sweetie.
Come take a photo with the director.

398
00:19:33,083 --> 00:19:34,708
I'd rather check on the villagers, Mom.

399
00:19:34,792 --> 00:19:36,500
In case they have more complaints.

400
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:40,125
- Alright. I'll call you later.
- Excuse me.

401
00:19:40,208 --> 00:19:41,167
[speaks indistinctly]

402
00:19:41,250 --> 00:19:43,875
Oh, okay. Please, come forward.

403
00:19:46,958 --> 00:19:49,375
- [music fades]
- [birds chirping]

404
00:19:51,542 --> 00:19:54,708
[Ang] From the Ruam Thai Party,
this is our help center's number.

405
00:19:54,792 --> 00:19:57,000
- You can call anytime.
- Thank you.

406
00:19:58,333 --> 00:20:00,917
From Dr. Atchara of the Ruam Thai Party.

407
00:20:01,792 --> 00:20:04,375
It's our party's help center.
You can call the number on the card.

408
00:20:04,458 --> 00:20:06,208
This is the number for our help center.

409
00:20:06,292 --> 00:20:08,542
If you need anything else,
please contact the party.

410
00:20:08,625 --> 00:20:10,333
- [woman 1] Get over here!
- [woman 2] Thief!

411
00:20:10,417 --> 00:20:12,000
- Thief! Somebody help!
- Quick! Catch him!

412
00:20:12,083 --> 00:20:14,083
- What? Ow! What is it?
- [women chattering]

413
00:20:14,167 --> 00:20:16,167
I'm not a thief. I'm a lawyer.

414
00:20:16,250 --> 00:20:17,208
[overlapping chatter]

415
00:20:17,292 --> 00:20:18,958
- Ma'am, please!
- I'm not a thief!

416
00:20:19,042 --> 00:20:22,208
- Calm down. What's going on?
- Please, listen to me. I'm not a thief.

417
00:20:22,292 --> 00:20:24,083
It's him! He was stealing
from Por's house.

418
00:20:24,167 --> 00:20:26,417
- [woman 2] That's right. I saw him.
- [woman 1] Yeah!

419
00:20:26,500 --> 00:20:27,458
I wasn't stealing.

420
00:20:27,542 --> 00:20:28,792
I am an eyewitness.

421
00:20:28,875 --> 00:20:30,458
- [Mek] No, I'm a lawyer!
- You little--

422
00:20:30,542 --> 00:20:31,500
Ma'am, please calm down.

423
00:20:31,583 --> 00:20:32,917
Ma'am, do you remember me?

424
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:34,625
I'm Dr. Atchara's daughter.

425
00:20:36,125 --> 00:20:38,250
Oh, right. This morning,
she was handing out supplies.

426
00:20:38,333 --> 00:20:39,625
- [Ang] That's right.
- Oh, yeah.

427
00:20:39,708 --> 00:20:42,667
This man is a friend of mine.
He's a lawyer, not a thief.

428
00:20:42,750 --> 00:20:44,125
- What?
- Well…

429
00:20:44,208 --> 00:20:47,208
- [chickens clucking]
- See? I told you.

430
00:20:47,292 --> 00:20:48,750
A handsome man like him?

431
00:20:48,833 --> 00:20:51,083
Are you hurt, dear? Wait, your tumbler.

432
00:20:51,167 --> 00:20:53,042
Oh, here it is. Are you hurt?

433
00:20:53,125 --> 00:20:55,375
- Here, let me help.
- I'm okay, thanks.

434
00:20:55,458 --> 00:20:58,542
If you're a lawyer, why were you
rummaging through Por's house?

435
00:20:58,625 --> 00:20:59,667
Yeah, good point.

436
00:20:59,750 --> 00:21:01,625
Does he have to go to court again?

437
00:21:01,708 --> 00:21:03,417
Something like that.

438
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:07,375
I knew it. I knew he'd get into trouble
one of these days.

439
00:21:07,458 --> 00:21:10,667
So who filed the complaint?
Was it Kuang or Juk?

440
00:21:12,375 --> 00:21:14,875
He was having trouble with those two?

441
00:21:14,958 --> 00:21:17,333
Yes. And plenty of others, too.

442
00:21:17,417 --> 00:21:19,500
He owes money to everyone around here.

443
00:21:19,583 --> 00:21:21,542
It's no surprise he got arrested.

444
00:21:21,625 --> 00:21:23,917
[woman 1] How much does he owe you?
Over 2,000?

445
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:26,083
[woman 2 chuckles] He owes me 3,600.

446
00:21:26,167 --> 00:21:28,000
What did he need all that money for?

447
00:21:28,083 --> 00:21:30,958
[woman 2] He spent it all
on his granddaughter.

448
00:21:31,042 --> 00:21:33,000
His son racked up huge baccarat debts…

449
00:21:33,083 --> 00:21:34,125
- Yes.
- …and just ran off.

450
00:21:34,208 --> 00:21:36,208
[woman 2] The debt, the granddaughter…

451
00:21:36,292 --> 00:21:38,042
He was left to handle everything.

452
00:21:38,125 --> 00:21:40,750
But he really does love
his granddaughter.

453
00:21:40,833 --> 00:21:43,375
It's a good thing the fire happened
on his day off.

454
00:21:43,458 --> 00:21:44,917
The guards were changing shifts.

455
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:47,833
So he got the day off
and took Kratai out.

456
00:21:47,917 --> 00:21:49,958
- Was he a security guard?
- [intriguing music playing]

457
00:21:50,042 --> 00:21:51,375
Where did he work as a guard?

458
00:21:51,458 --> 00:21:54,833
Oh, at the waste processing plant
that burned down.

459
00:21:56,958 --> 00:21:59,708
Wait. If Por gets sued and goes to jail,

460
00:22:00,208 --> 00:22:01,833
how will Kratai survive?

461
00:22:01,917 --> 00:22:04,333
- [woman 1] How should I know?
- Excuse me, ma'am.

462
00:22:04,417 --> 00:22:07,500
Could you tell me the story
about Kratai's father again?

463
00:22:07,583 --> 00:22:08,625
[music fades]

464
00:22:08,708 --> 00:22:10,708
[Ang] So he claimed
to be the factory owner?

465
00:22:10,792 --> 00:22:14,958
[Mek] He said he's a managing director
and a shareholder. Can you believe that?

466
00:22:15,042 --> 00:22:17,958
[Ang] The waste at that factory
is all electronic.

467
00:22:18,042 --> 00:22:18,958
[Mek] Hmm.

468
00:22:19,042 --> 00:22:21,375
It must have been illegally imported.

469
00:22:21,458 --> 00:22:22,458
[Mek] Hmm…

470
00:22:22,542 --> 00:22:24,917
And to open it in a residential area,

471
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:27,375
the real owner must be well-connected.

472
00:22:28,708 --> 00:22:30,917
Getting your human rights lawyer
blood pumping again, huh?

473
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:32,917
- [chuckles softly]
- Do you miss it?

474
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:36,125
I still secretly help the labor union
with their cases.

475
00:22:36,208 --> 00:22:39,083
But my party work is so demanding.

476
00:22:40,583 --> 00:22:42,042
It's a strange sight.

477
00:22:44,292 --> 00:22:46,000
I never thought I'd see it.

478
00:22:46,083 --> 00:22:47,958
[chuckles] Aren't you hot?

479
00:22:49,167 --> 00:22:51,708
I've never heard you use
your mom's name before.

480
00:22:51,792 --> 00:22:53,375
I don't like to.

481
00:22:53,458 --> 00:22:55,917
But mentioning her name
makes it easier to connect with people.

482
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:57,042
[Mek] Hmm…

483
00:23:00,375 --> 00:23:02,083
So, are you getting used to it?

484
00:23:05,292 --> 00:23:06,625
What about you?

485
00:23:06,708 --> 00:23:09,292
Has taking on public defender cases
made life any better?

486
00:23:13,542 --> 00:23:14,583
It's okay.

487
00:23:22,125 --> 00:23:23,542
It's only been three months.

488
00:23:25,333 --> 00:23:27,292
How okay did you expect me to be?

489
00:23:30,292 --> 00:23:32,917
[soft somber music playing]

490
00:23:36,833 --> 00:23:38,042
What did I do wrong?

491
00:23:39,708 --> 00:23:41,292
Can you tell me now?

492
00:23:45,875 --> 00:23:47,208
I have to get back to work.

493
00:23:47,292 --> 00:23:48,542
Sorry.

494
00:23:53,292 --> 00:23:55,000
- [Mek] <i>Ang.</i>
- [Ang] <i>Mek, just go home.</i>

495
00:23:55,083 --> 00:23:57,250
[Mek] <i>Go home? We need to talk first.</i>

496
00:23:57,333 --> 00:23:58,375
<i>Ang, don't walk away.</i>

497
00:23:58,458 --> 00:23:59,500
3 MONTHS AGO

498
00:23:59,583 --> 00:24:00,833
You don't even answer my calls.

499
00:24:00,917 --> 00:24:03,000
- I'm busy, Mek.
- Busy with what?

500
00:24:03,083 --> 00:24:05,292
You're not doing anything.
Working on what?

501
00:24:05,375 --> 00:24:06,958
Why are you going back on your word?

502
00:24:07,042 --> 00:24:09,000
Aren't you ashamed? Seriously.

503
00:24:09,083 --> 00:24:10,667
Working for a corrupt party like this?

504
00:24:10,750 --> 00:24:12,292
This is my mother's party.

505
00:24:12,375 --> 00:24:13,625
This work is important.

506
00:24:13,708 --> 00:24:17,417
What about your work at the law center?
The people there weren't important?

507
00:24:18,417 --> 00:24:20,583
So many people
entrusted their lives to you.

508
00:24:21,083 --> 00:24:23,792
Like Tle's case. Who's handling it now?

509
00:24:23,875 --> 00:24:24,917
The speech case?

510
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:27,667
Are you just going to let them all
go to jail?

511
00:24:27,750 --> 00:24:29,792
[soft tense music playing]

512
00:24:34,292 --> 00:24:36,750
You left the law center
because of me, didn't you?

513
00:24:40,917 --> 00:24:42,250
What did I do wrong?

514
00:24:43,375 --> 00:24:44,917
Tell me just one thing.

515
00:24:46,500 --> 00:24:48,667
Ever since you came back
from the party on the boat,

516
00:24:48,750 --> 00:24:50,000
you haven't been the same.

517
00:24:51,167 --> 00:24:52,542
What exactly happened on that boat?

518
00:24:52,625 --> 00:24:53,833
I wanted to break up.

519
00:25:00,333 --> 00:25:01,792
You didn't do anything wrong.

520
00:25:01,875 --> 00:25:03,250
[music concludes]

521
00:25:03,333 --> 00:25:04,792
I just wanted to break up.

522
00:25:12,500 --> 00:25:15,417
- [footsteps departing]
- [soft pensive music playing]

523
00:25:35,667 --> 00:25:37,542
[soft pensive music continues]

524
00:25:41,958 --> 00:25:43,792
[chains jangling]

525
00:25:45,875 --> 00:25:48,917
Sir, I know you didn't do it.

526
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:51,375
But I don't know what they offered you.

527
00:25:51,458 --> 00:25:53,042
But please, think carefully.

528
00:25:53,125 --> 00:25:54,792
You won't be there for Kratai.

529
00:25:54,875 --> 00:25:55,792
[music concludes]

530
00:25:55,875 --> 00:25:57,792
You're paying off
your son's baccarat debt, right?

531
00:25:57,875 --> 00:26:00,667
So you had to take the fall
for the factory owners.

532
00:26:00,750 --> 00:26:02,000
Please, think this through.

533
00:26:02,083 --> 00:26:03,375
If you go to prison now,

534
00:26:03,458 --> 00:26:06,333
the only one left to look after Kratai
will be your son.

535
00:26:08,208 --> 00:26:12,042
Right? That lump sum you got,
how many years of tuition will it cover?

536
00:26:12,125 --> 00:26:14,417
But if you retract your confession today…

537
00:26:14,500 --> 00:26:15,500
Sir.

538
00:26:15,583 --> 00:26:18,375
I promise I'll do everything
to get you the lightest sentence possible.

539
00:26:18,458 --> 00:26:20,083
[Aon] What are you doing?

540
00:26:20,167 --> 00:26:21,458
Please trust me.

541
00:26:23,958 --> 00:26:25,708
I'm speaking with my client.
What's with you?

542
00:26:25,792 --> 00:26:27,250
- He's my father.
- Calm down, son.

543
00:26:27,333 --> 00:26:28,917
- What did you say to him?
- [Mek] Officer.

544
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:31,458
- None of your damn business!
- How did you let a drunk man in?

545
00:26:31,542 --> 00:26:33,792
Dad, don't listen to him. I told you.

546
00:26:33,875 --> 00:26:34,958
Officer, please remove him.

547
00:26:35,042 --> 00:26:37,125
- [officer] Sir, please leave.
- Are you messing with me?

548
00:26:37,208 --> 00:26:38,375
[officer] Please step outside.

549
00:26:38,458 --> 00:26:40,542
I need to talk to my father.
I have the right!

550
00:26:40,625 --> 00:26:41,542
Dad!

551
00:26:41,625 --> 00:26:43,708
- Don't talk to him anymore!
- Sir, trust me.

552
00:26:43,792 --> 00:26:46,167
The only person you need to think about
is Kratai.

553
00:26:46,250 --> 00:26:48,250
- [Aon shouting indistinctly]
- Okay?

554
00:26:48,333 --> 00:26:49,417
Please trust me.

555
00:26:51,375 --> 00:26:53,458
The court will explain
the defendant's rights

556
00:26:53,542 --> 00:26:55,708
before proceeding with the trial.

557
00:26:56,792 --> 00:26:59,333
Do you plead guilty to all charges?

558
00:27:09,583 --> 00:27:10,708
Well, defendant?

559
00:27:20,333 --> 00:27:21,333
[Mek softly] Sir.

560
00:27:32,125 --> 00:27:33,125
[judge] Defendant.

561
00:27:34,417 --> 00:27:36,750
The defendant pleads not guilty
to all charges.

562
00:27:36,833 --> 00:27:37,917
Let me explain.

563
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:40,958
From the beginning, the defendant
has not had a chance to consult a lawyer.

564
00:27:41,042 --> 00:27:42,875
And I believe that is his basic right.

565
00:27:42,958 --> 00:27:46,167
If he is truly not guilty, he should have
the right to fight, correct?

566
00:27:46,250 --> 00:27:47,750
Today, I've prepared documents that I…

567
00:27:47,833 --> 00:27:50,083
I am addressing the defendant.
Let him answer.

568
00:27:51,750 --> 00:27:53,375
So, how do you plead, defendant?

569
00:27:54,792 --> 00:27:57,833
[clock ticking faintly]

570
00:28:08,042 --> 00:28:09,083
Sir.

571
00:28:09,625 --> 00:28:10,750
[Por] I…

572
00:28:13,917 --> 00:28:16,750
I… I'm not guilty.

573
00:28:16,833 --> 00:28:19,167
[soft pensive music playing]

574
00:28:19,250 --> 00:28:21,125
I'll fight the charges.

575
00:28:22,917 --> 00:28:24,667
[breathes deeply]

576
00:28:28,625 --> 00:28:29,500
[grunts softly]

577
00:28:37,500 --> 00:28:40,417
Sir, I'll start the bail process
right away.

578
00:28:40,500 --> 00:28:42,333
Then we can fight this from the outside.

579
00:28:42,417 --> 00:28:43,917
Thank you so much.

580
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:46,208
[chains jangling]

581
00:28:48,375 --> 00:28:49,458
[Techin] Hey.

582
00:28:50,917 --> 00:28:52,292
Just so you know,

583
00:28:52,917 --> 00:28:54,708
this case is bigger than you think.

584
00:28:55,292 --> 00:28:56,333
Bigger how?

585
00:28:56,417 --> 00:28:58,667
I'm just doing my job.

586
00:28:58,750 --> 00:29:00,583
- [music fades]
- What is wrong with you?

587
00:29:00,667 --> 00:29:02,208
I already told you, didn't I?

588
00:29:02,292 --> 00:29:04,500
That I won't let him go to prison.

589
00:29:05,250 --> 00:29:06,125
[scoffs]

590
00:29:06,208 --> 00:29:08,625
But are you going to tell me
who the factory owner is?

591
00:29:08,708 --> 00:29:10,042
Some guy with dirty money?

592
00:29:10,792 --> 00:29:11,958
Or is it your dad?

593
00:29:14,583 --> 00:29:16,125
I gave you a friendly warning.

594
00:29:16,917 --> 00:29:18,708
But you just wouldn't listen.

595
00:29:18,792 --> 00:29:21,125
[foreboding music playing]

596
00:29:29,625 --> 00:29:31,750
[foreboding music continues]

597
00:29:36,875 --> 00:29:37,958
[seat belt clicks]

598
00:30:16,458 --> 00:30:17,583
[Techin] Dad.

599
00:30:18,667 --> 00:30:20,292
About the waste plant fire case,

600
00:30:20,375 --> 00:30:22,792
it might drag on a little longer
than we thought.

601
00:30:24,625 --> 00:30:27,750
My senior, Mek, has taken the case.

602
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:30,042
He's…

603
00:30:31,250 --> 00:30:32,958
But don't worry, Dad.

604
00:30:33,042 --> 00:30:34,500
I can definitely handle him.

605
00:30:35,917 --> 00:30:38,875
That 3-iron I gave you.
Have you been practicing?

606
00:30:38,958 --> 00:30:41,625
[unsettling music playing]

607
00:30:58,417 --> 00:31:00,000
[bucket clangs]

608
00:31:02,750 --> 00:31:03,833
[Anan] Focus.

609
00:31:06,208 --> 00:31:07,500
You see…

610
00:31:08,625 --> 00:31:10,125
not everyone gets equal opportunities.

611
00:31:10,208 --> 00:31:11,542
[tense music playing]

612
00:31:11,625 --> 00:31:15,125
Every time someone gives you
a chance to do something,

613
00:31:15,208 --> 00:31:16,917
you must remember that…

614
00:31:17,625 --> 00:31:20,500
it's because they trust you.

615
00:31:21,458 --> 00:31:24,250
If you give someone your word,
you have to keep it.

616
00:31:26,583 --> 00:31:28,333
Because if you can't…

617
00:31:32,083 --> 00:31:35,500
you won't be the one
who ends up the most disappointed.

618
00:31:37,333 --> 00:31:39,042
Do you understand what I'm saying?

619
00:31:45,958 --> 00:31:49,833
[music builds]

620
00:31:52,167 --> 00:31:53,167
[golf club thwacks]

621
00:31:53,250 --> 00:31:54,667
[music fades]

622
00:31:54,750 --> 00:31:56,875
[foreboding music playing]

623
00:32:16,750 --> 00:32:18,167
[music fades]

624
00:32:18,250 --> 00:32:22,667
- [pen clicking]
- [indistinct chatter]

625
00:32:27,583 --> 00:32:29,958
[cell phone ringing]

626
00:32:30,042 --> 00:32:32,375
TAE - CLASS OF '49

627
00:32:33,250 --> 00:32:34,958
- [cell phone clicks]
- [ringing stops]

628
00:32:39,292 --> 00:32:40,667
[cell phone buzzes, chimes]

629
00:32:43,792 --> 00:32:46,958
DEPOSIT: 300,000 BAHT
OCT 14, 2025

630
00:32:56,875 --> 00:32:58,167
[dial tone ringing]

631
00:32:58,250 --> 00:32:59,583
[sighs]

632
00:33:00,917 --> 00:33:02,375
[dial tone continues ringing]

633
00:33:04,625 --> 00:33:06,542
Is this the only way you know
how to play?

634
00:33:06,625 --> 00:33:07,750
[Techin] <i>Play what?</i>

635
00:33:07,833 --> 00:33:10,000
I'm not playing. I'm dead serious.

636
00:33:10,833 --> 00:33:11,917
[snickers]

637
00:33:12,500 --> 00:33:14,292
What I sent you was just a deposit.

638
00:33:15,333 --> 00:33:18,333
The moment you drop the case,
I'll transfer the rest.

639
00:33:18,417 --> 00:33:22,417
Listen, if you don't quit this shit,
I'll report you to the Lawyers Council.

640
00:33:22,500 --> 00:33:23,583
[Techin] <i>I knew it.</i>

641
00:33:23,667 --> 00:33:25,875
<i>Money alone could never sway</i>
<i>a good man like you.</i>

642
00:33:26,625 --> 00:33:28,625
I've prepared a little surprise for you.

643
00:33:29,667 --> 00:33:33,042
Do you want to know
why Ang broke up with you?

644
00:33:35,042 --> 00:33:36,583
What does Ang have to do with this?

645
00:33:36,667 --> 00:33:38,333
[Techin] <i>Remember three months ago?</i>

646
00:33:38,417 --> 00:33:40,167
<i>After that party on the boat,</i>

647
00:33:40,250 --> 00:33:41,875
<i>Ang started acting weird, right?</i>

648
00:33:43,167 --> 00:33:45,000
<i>And then she left you.</i>

649
00:33:46,042 --> 00:33:48,000
<i>Why was that? </i>[chuckles]

650
00:33:48,083 --> 00:33:49,917
[tense music playing]

651
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:51,875
Ang would never dare tell you.

652
00:33:52,667 --> 00:33:53,792
But I will.

653
00:33:53,875 --> 00:33:55,042
Come and see me.

654
00:33:55,125 --> 00:33:57,000
<i>I'm at my house in Saraburi.</i>

655
00:33:57,083 --> 00:33:58,250
<i>You remember it, right?</i>

656
00:33:59,542 --> 00:34:01,500
<i>But you only have until tonight.</i>

657
00:34:01,583 --> 00:34:03,167
<i>If you don't show up,</i>

658
00:34:03,250 --> 00:34:06,167
you'll just have to guess
what I'll do with what I know.

659
00:34:11,167 --> 00:34:12,375
[cell phone chimes]

660
00:34:15,750 --> 00:34:18,208
[music rises]

661
00:34:19,792 --> 00:34:20,708
[Mek] <i>What is it?</i>

662
00:34:21,750 --> 00:34:22,708
<i>What happened?</i>

663
00:34:22,792 --> 00:34:24,167
[Ang] <i>Nothing happened.</i>

664
00:34:24,250 --> 00:34:25,708
[Mek] <i>Were you lying to me?</i>

665
00:34:26,250 --> 00:34:27,792
[music fades]

666
00:34:27,875 --> 00:34:29,833
[Mek] It was on the boat, wasn't it?

667
00:34:30,417 --> 00:34:32,000
What happened at the party?

668
00:34:33,500 --> 00:34:35,167
Did somebody do something to you?

669
00:34:35,875 --> 00:34:38,042
You have to tell me.
I can help you fix this.

670
00:34:38,125 --> 00:34:39,125
[Ang] You can't, Mek.

671
00:34:39,208 --> 00:34:41,292
Even if I told you, you couldn't help.

672
00:34:41,375 --> 00:34:44,125
[foreboding music playing]

673
00:34:45,792 --> 00:34:48,333
[engine revving]

674
00:34:59,792 --> 00:35:02,250
[foreboding music continues]

675
00:35:07,167 --> 00:35:08,292
[brakes screeching]

676
00:35:09,000 --> 00:35:10,042
[gearshift clunks]

677
00:35:10,125 --> 00:35:11,125
[handbrake creaks]

678
00:35:18,542 --> 00:35:20,875
[insects trilling]

679
00:35:29,750 --> 00:35:32,125
[Techin] That was fast.
You must've floored it.

680
00:35:32,667 --> 00:35:34,917
- [music concludes]
- Wow. Less than two hours.

681
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:36,083
That's the new record.

682
00:35:36,167 --> 00:35:39,042
Here's your money.
Now, what do you have to say?

683
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:42,875
Since you drove all the way here,

684
00:35:43,583 --> 00:35:45,000
how about we play a hole?

685
00:35:45,083 --> 00:35:46,625
I just got a new caddie, too.

686
00:35:46,708 --> 00:35:47,792
Hey!

687
00:35:48,583 --> 00:35:50,625
If you have nothing to say, I'm leaving.

688
00:35:51,167 --> 00:35:53,583
Alright, calm down, Mek.

689
00:35:53,667 --> 00:35:56,250
We can talk while we play.
It's not that hard.

690
00:35:56,958 --> 00:35:58,208
This is Nay Oo.

691
00:35:58,708 --> 00:36:00,583
- You bitch!
- [tense music playing]

692
00:36:00,667 --> 00:36:02,375
[Techin] I told you not to drag it!

693
00:36:02,458 --> 00:36:04,333
Don't you understand what I said?

694
00:36:04,417 --> 00:36:05,792
- What is wrong with you?
- Hey!

695
00:36:05,875 --> 00:36:08,125
The bag's heavy as hell.
Why don't you carry it?

696
00:36:08,208 --> 00:36:10,958
Fine. You want to play so bad? One hole.

697
00:36:11,875 --> 00:36:13,417
That's it. [chuckles]

698
00:36:14,083 --> 00:36:15,333
After you.

699
00:36:16,750 --> 00:36:18,083
Go.

700
00:36:18,167 --> 00:36:19,375
[Mek] Here, let me get that.

701
00:36:19,458 --> 00:36:21,292
I'm fine, sir.

702
00:36:23,125 --> 00:36:25,333
[bag rustling]

703
00:36:27,375 --> 00:36:28,833
[music concludes]

704
00:36:28,917 --> 00:36:32,250
- [indistinct clamor over radio]
- [radio host speaking indistinctly]

705
00:36:33,500 --> 00:36:36,500
- [indistinct clamor continues]
- [radio host continues speaking]

706
00:36:43,583 --> 00:36:44,708
[chuckles]

707
00:36:44,792 --> 00:36:46,333
Nailed it.

708
00:36:47,833 --> 00:36:49,083
Show me what you've got.

709
00:36:58,833 --> 00:36:59,958
[golf club thwacks]

710
00:37:00,042 --> 00:37:02,708
Damn. You really crushed that.

711
00:37:03,208 --> 00:37:06,042
You picturing my head
when you swing? [laughs]

712
00:37:06,125 --> 00:37:08,750
Still, your form's not bad. Passable.

713
00:37:11,792 --> 00:37:13,875
So, how many years has it been, Mek?

714
00:37:14,958 --> 00:37:16,958
I never see you at the reunions.

715
00:37:19,208 --> 00:37:20,500
You still play much?

716
00:37:21,417 --> 00:37:24,417
So, what is it?
Are you going to tell me or not?

717
00:37:24,500 --> 00:37:26,417
What's the rush?

718
00:37:27,583 --> 00:37:28,625
[scoffs]

719
00:37:30,083 --> 00:37:31,333
Alright.

720
00:37:35,375 --> 00:37:36,458
[zipper opens]

721
00:37:39,875 --> 00:37:41,458
[zipper closes]

722
00:37:42,375 --> 00:37:44,708
[unsettling music playing]

723
00:37:45,583 --> 00:37:46,833
You want it or not?

724
00:37:47,708 --> 00:37:50,167
[scoffs] What the hell
are you so paranoid about?

725
00:37:50,250 --> 00:37:52,750
Huh? You know I'm not usually this nice.

726
00:37:53,583 --> 00:37:54,958
Don't you want to know…

727
00:37:55,667 --> 00:37:57,167
why Ang broke up with you?

728
00:37:58,542 --> 00:37:59,792
The answer's in here.

729
00:38:00,292 --> 00:38:01,333
[folder thuds]

730
00:38:15,542 --> 00:38:19,208
MYSTERIOUS BODY
FOUND IN CHAO PHRAYA RIVER

731
00:38:23,667 --> 00:38:25,667
Hey, what the hell is this?

732
00:38:27,042 --> 00:38:29,708
Do you remember the date
of that party on the boat?

733
00:38:31,625 --> 00:38:32,833
I'll answer for you.

734
00:38:32,917 --> 00:38:34,083
July 1st.

735
00:38:34,750 --> 00:38:36,042
Check the date in the article.

736
00:38:36,875 --> 00:38:37,958
July 10th.

737
00:38:38,542 --> 00:38:40,500
"The body of a foreign woman discovered…

738
00:38:40,583 --> 00:38:42,500
floating in the Chao Phraya River."

739
00:38:43,375 --> 00:38:45,125
And I've got something else.

740
00:38:45,625 --> 00:38:48,042
An exclusive, just for you.

741
00:38:49,583 --> 00:38:52,917
What are you trying to say?
And what does Ang have to do with this?

742
00:38:53,458 --> 00:38:54,750
[Techin] At the party,

743
00:38:55,667 --> 00:38:57,833
a waitress on that boat died.

744
00:38:59,792 --> 00:39:01,250
And on a boat that small…

745
00:39:01,958 --> 00:39:03,375
You think Ang didn't know?

746
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:09,292
Of course, she knew…

747
00:39:10,792 --> 00:39:12,500
but why did she cover it up?

748
00:39:17,125 --> 00:39:19,667
[chuckles]
She'd just gotten into politics.

749
00:39:20,208 --> 00:39:23,583
If word got out that she helped
dispose of a body… [clicks tongue]

750
00:39:23,667 --> 00:39:24,958
Game over.

751
00:39:25,042 --> 00:39:27,833
You're using this to get me
to drop the factory case, aren't you?

752
00:39:27,917 --> 00:39:29,833
[scoffs] I didn't say that.

753
00:39:29,917 --> 00:39:31,083
But maybe.

754
00:39:32,500 --> 00:39:33,958
You don't have the guts, Techin.

755
00:39:34,042 --> 00:39:35,417
If you leak this, you go down.

756
00:39:35,500 --> 00:39:37,917
So do your dad and everyone on that boat.

757
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:40,083
Oh! Damn it.

758
00:39:40,167 --> 00:39:42,042
Enough talk. Go get the ball.

759
00:39:44,958 --> 00:39:45,958
You're right.

760
00:39:46,042 --> 00:39:47,583
I have no intention of leaking anything.

761
00:39:47,667 --> 00:39:49,417
Neither does anyone else on the boat.

762
00:39:49,500 --> 00:39:52,083
Why would they risk
getting themselves into trouble?

763
00:39:52,875 --> 00:39:53,875
[scoffs]

764
00:39:54,500 --> 00:39:57,042
Everyone on that boat was a VVIP.

765
00:39:58,000 --> 00:40:01,500
No one's stupid enough to risk it all
for one Burmese girl.

766
00:40:02,958 --> 00:40:05,792
But someone with nothing to lose?

767
00:40:06,792 --> 00:40:08,792
Someone with absolutely nothing to lose.

768
00:40:09,667 --> 00:40:10,958
You never know

769
00:40:11,042 --> 00:40:14,125
when they might turn on you.

770
00:40:14,208 --> 00:40:16,417
- What are you talking about?
- [Techin] Hey, wait.

771
00:40:19,833 --> 00:40:21,292
Remember this woman?

772
00:40:24,958 --> 00:40:28,500
Was she on the boat with you
the night your sister died?

773
00:40:31,958 --> 00:40:34,542
[tense dramatic music playing]

774
00:40:36,125 --> 00:40:38,125
- [Nay Oo yelps]
- [Mek] Hey! What are you doing?

775
00:40:38,208 --> 00:40:39,292
Are you okay?

776
00:40:39,375 --> 00:40:41,667
- [Nay Oo whimpers]
- [Mek] What the hell is wrong with you?!

777
00:40:41,750 --> 00:40:44,917
Now do you get it?
The waitress who died was her sister.

778
00:40:45,000 --> 00:40:47,042
And she was on the boat that night.

779
00:40:47,625 --> 00:40:51,000
If she decides to talk,
everyone from that boat goes down.

780
00:40:51,583 --> 00:40:54,292
But if she disappears, it's all over.

781
00:40:55,750 --> 00:40:58,667
What the hell are you saying?
Who's going to disappear?

782
00:40:58,750 --> 00:41:00,833
[music intensifies]

783
00:41:01,958 --> 00:41:03,917
[Mek] What the hell are you doing?!

784
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:05,250
[groans]

785
00:41:05,333 --> 00:41:07,375
[discordant tense music playing]

786
00:41:07,458 --> 00:41:09,333
- [gunshots]
- [glass shatters]

787
00:41:09,417 --> 00:41:11,833
- [breathes shakily]
- [high-pitched ringing]

788
00:41:11,917 --> 00:41:13,167
[woman echoing] Help!

789
00:41:13,958 --> 00:41:16,250
[breathes shakily]

790
00:41:16,333 --> 00:41:17,667
What the hell is wrong with you?

791
00:41:17,750 --> 00:41:19,167
- Are you hurt?
- [Techin laughs]

792
00:41:19,250 --> 00:41:20,500
[Nay Oo sobs]

793
00:41:20,583 --> 00:41:22,125
That was just practice.

794
00:41:22,917 --> 00:41:24,417
This time, it's for real.

795
00:41:24,500 --> 00:41:27,958
- Why are you doing this?
- I'm helping Ang eliminate the evidence.

796
00:41:28,458 --> 00:41:29,708
Her sister is dead.

797
00:41:30,208 --> 00:41:32,375
How long do you think she'll stay quiet?

798
00:41:32,458 --> 00:41:35,083
Are you kidding me? Look at her.
She's scared to death.

799
00:41:35,167 --> 00:41:36,792
You won't say anything, right?

800
00:41:36,875 --> 00:41:40,000
[sobbing] I swear. I won't say anything.

801
00:41:40,083 --> 00:41:42,208
I'll go back home to Myanmar.

802
00:41:42,292 --> 00:41:43,542
- I swear, sir.
- [chuckles]

803
00:41:43,625 --> 00:41:45,917
[Mek] You know the court
won't give her word any weight.

804
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:47,708
It's just the word of one witness, right?

805
00:41:47,792 --> 00:41:49,917
And she's the victim's relative.
You know that.

806
00:41:51,917 --> 00:41:53,875
I don't think that's good enough.

807
00:41:54,750 --> 00:41:56,042
Don't!

808
00:41:56,708 --> 00:41:58,125
You want me to drop the case?

809
00:41:58,208 --> 00:42:00,417
Fine. I'll go sign the papers right now.

810
00:42:00,500 --> 00:42:02,208
Do you think I'm an idiot?

811
00:42:02,792 --> 00:42:05,542
You drop the case,
then you just have your client--

812
00:42:05,625 --> 00:42:08,292
- [thud]
- [grunts, coughs]

813
00:42:08,375 --> 00:42:10,583
- [Nay Oo sobbing]
- [music builds]

814
00:42:11,458 --> 00:42:12,417
[Nay Oo sobs]

815
00:42:14,375 --> 00:42:16,000
[music crescendos]

816
00:42:16,083 --> 00:42:18,667
- [gunshot echoes]
- [music concludes]

817
00:42:18,750 --> 00:42:20,083
[Techin laughs]

818
00:42:20,167 --> 00:42:21,583
[in English] Nice shot, bro.

819
00:42:21,667 --> 00:42:23,667
[somber music playing]

820
00:42:23,750 --> 00:42:25,917
[Techin in Thai]
We're in the same boat now.

821
00:42:26,875 --> 00:42:28,917
If the cops test this gun,

822
00:42:29,000 --> 00:42:30,917
they'll find both of our fingerprints.

823
00:42:32,083 --> 00:42:34,458
That means there are two suspects.

824
00:42:35,625 --> 00:42:37,667
You'll be going to prison
right alongside me.

825
00:42:37,750 --> 00:42:38,625
[snickers]

826
00:42:39,375 --> 00:42:41,583
Stay away from the waste plant case.

827
00:42:52,500 --> 00:42:54,750
What are you so shocked about, huh?

828
00:42:56,042 --> 00:42:59,042
You're acting like you've never seen
someone get shot before.

829
00:42:59,917 --> 00:43:01,333
[echoing gunshots]

830
00:43:02,375 --> 00:43:04,000
- [Techin] Oh…
- [breathes shakily]

831
00:43:04,083 --> 00:43:06,375
[Techin] Does little Mek miss his mommy?

832
00:43:06,458 --> 00:43:07,667
[laughs]

833
00:43:07,750 --> 00:43:09,125
I feel you, bro.

834
00:43:11,000 --> 00:43:13,208
But your family's story is something else.

835
00:43:13,292 --> 00:43:16,000
Your dad's a legendary judge,
isn't he? [laughs]

836
00:43:18,292 --> 00:43:20,042
Sacrificed his wife for his principles.

837
00:43:20,125 --> 00:43:21,458
[Nay Oo yells]

838
00:43:21,542 --> 00:43:22,542
[groans]

839
00:43:23,708 --> 00:43:24,625
[shrieks]

840
00:43:24,708 --> 00:43:26,417
- [breathes shakily]
- [music concludes]

841
00:43:26,500 --> 00:43:27,458
[Nay Oo grunts]

842
00:43:28,583 --> 00:43:30,875
- [sobbing]
- [heavy thuds]

843
00:43:32,125 --> 00:43:33,958
- [wailing]
- [squelching]

844
00:43:34,042 --> 00:43:36,333
[dark tense music playing]

845
00:43:39,375 --> 00:43:41,208
- That's enough.
- [music fades]

846
00:43:42,000 --> 00:43:43,833
- That's enough.
- [sobs]

847
00:43:43,917 --> 00:43:45,667
[foreboding music playing]

848
00:43:45,750 --> 00:43:47,500
[sobbing]

849
00:43:50,042 --> 00:43:51,750
[whimpering]

850
00:43:59,833 --> 00:44:02,042
[breathes shakily]

851
00:44:05,250 --> 00:44:07,083
[Nay Oo sobbing]

852
00:44:15,375 --> 00:44:17,917
[Mek breathing shakily]

853
00:44:24,250 --> 00:44:26,167
[man echoing] Sir! Help me!

854
00:44:27,958 --> 00:44:29,833
[reporter 1] <i>Our reporter</i>
<i>on the scene confirms</i>

855
00:44:29,917 --> 00:44:31,833
<i>the suspect has been apprehended.</i>

856
00:44:31,917 --> 00:44:33,583
<i>He was arrested at the scene.</i>

857
00:44:33,667 --> 00:44:35,917
<i>The suspect has been identified</i>
<i>as Mek Piriyawich.</i>

858
00:44:36,000 --> 00:44:38,083
[reporter 2]<i> We have a report</i>
<i>coming from our sources.</i>

859
00:44:38,167 --> 00:44:41,125
<i>The victim was Techin Methaneepaisal.</i>

860
00:44:41,208 --> 00:44:43,875
The victim was the son of Pol. Gen. Anan.

861
00:44:43,958 --> 00:44:46,625
That's Police General Anan Methaneepaisal.

862
00:44:46,708 --> 00:44:51,250
[reporter 1] <i>The police currently have</i>
<i>the suspect in custody for questioning.</i>

863
00:44:51,333 --> 00:44:54,625
<i>A decision regarding bail</i>
<i>is currently pending.</i>

864
00:44:54,708 --> 00:44:55,792
[sound becomes muffled]

865
00:44:55,875 --> 00:44:57,833
[foreboding music continues]

866
00:44:59,250 --> 00:45:00,833
[dramatic musical sting plays]

867
00:45:00,917 --> 00:45:02,750
[Nay Oo sobbing, echoing]

868
00:45:02,833 --> 00:45:06,458
[echoing heavy thuds]

869
00:45:06,542 --> 00:45:07,750
[Nay Oo shrieks]

870
00:45:07,833 --> 00:45:10,917
[music turns intriguing]

871
00:45:21,417 --> 00:45:22,833
We don't have much time.

872
00:45:22,917 --> 00:45:25,000
If you want to survive, listen carefully.

873
00:45:26,833 --> 00:45:29,208
Because I'm your only way out.

874
00:45:29,292 --> 00:45:32,042
[dramatic music overlapping]

875
00:45:35,208 --> 00:45:38,250
[music intensifies]

876
00:46:43,625 --> 00:46:47,542
[dark tense music playing]

877
00:47:53,833 --> 00:47:56,250
[music concludes]
